6:03:22Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "https://github.com/mathiasose/slacker_log_handler/blob/master/slacker_log_handler/__init__.py#L27\r\n\r\nSlacker throws an error where there is invalid API_KEY. It'd be nice to be able to handle this error or not throw error, without it complete app collapses", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mathiasose/slacker_log_handler/issues/13", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mathiasose/slacker_log_handler", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mathiasose/slacker_log_handler/issues/13/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mathiasose/slacker_log_handler/issues/13/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mathiasose/slacker_log_handler/issues/13/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/mathiasose/slacker_log_handler/issues/13", "id": 190814476, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUxOTA4MTQ0NzY=", "number": 13, "title": "Formatting LogRecord message before posting to Slack", "user": {"login": "cvng", "id": 7042907, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjcwNDI5MDc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/7042907?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/cvng", "html_url": "https://github.com/cvng", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cvng/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cvng/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cvng/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cvng/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cvng/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cvng/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cvng/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cvng/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cvng/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2016-11-21T19:36:41Z", "updated_at": "2016-11-23T19:17:44Z", "closed_at": "2016-11-23T14:15:59Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Since we're using [#slack](https://slack.com/) for logging, it would be nice to have the ability to format messages before posting.\r\n\r\nThis can be achieved by exposing `message` in a function we can subclass.\r\nhttps://github.com/mathiasose/slacker_log_handler/blob/master/slacker_log_handler/__init__.py#L32\r\n\r\n```python\r\nclass SlackerLogHandler(Handler):\r\n    def build_msg(self, record):\r\n        return record.getMessage()\r\n\r\n    def emit(self, record):\r\n        message = str(self.build_msg(record))\r\n        # [...]\r\n```\r\n\r\n```python\r\nclass CustomLogHandler(SlackerLogHandler):\r\n    def build_msg(self, record):\r\n        message = \"> New message :\\n\" + record.getMessage()\r\n        return message\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd for the settings :\r\n\r\n```python\r\nLOGGING = {\r\n    # [...]\r\n    'handlers': {\r\n        'slack-info': {\r\n            # [...]\r\n            'class': 'path.to.my.CustomLogHandler',\r\n        },\r\n    },\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.LogRecord\r\nhttps://get.slack.help/hc/en-us/articles/202288908-Format-your-messages\r\n\r\nI can open a PR if needed \ud83d\udc4d ", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}]}